			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Bards and Shaman unite....<a name="39769"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">May 13 04 10:41 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I have been quite annoyed the past while over the badgering of Shaman for haste when a Bard is around.  There have been a few topics regarding this issue, but when it comes down to it 90% of the time the Shaman's mana is totally wasted and for this I am deeply troubled.  Here's how it usually goes (using an LDoN group as an example):
<br />

<br />
Group: Warrior, Wizzie, Ranger, Cleric/Druid, Bard, Shaman
<br />

<br />
All are buffed and what does the Shaman cast??? Talisman of Alacrity 50% haste.
<br />

<br />
First battle:
<br />
Bard sings zek 60% haste, CotM 30% overhaste
<br />
Bard Epic procs for an added 55% haste with str and atk boost
<br />

<br />
Battle continues, epic keeps procing and the Bard keeps singing.
<br />

<br />
Warrior notices that Talisman of Alacrity is fading and says, &quot;Haste is fading&quot;
<br />

<br />
At this point I am totally flabourgasted because Dance of the Blade is still active, and has been after the first mob, and I'm still singing.  
<br />
I have heard some say that they like to have that initial haste while the bard gets their songs going.  This is a totally pathetic response since DotB lasts 2.5 minutes and is refreshed so often I hardly notice it drop at all, unless I'm idle for 2.5 minutes and if it takes me that long to bring a mob into camp then I should yield the pulling to someone else.
<br />

<br />
I guess that I wouldn't be so bothered if the Shaman used swift like the wind instead of Talisman, but 99.999% of the time I see Talisman and it's a waste of mana and a buff slot.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=641487">Muse Ellorra Dannen</a><br>
Bard of the 65th Song<br><br>

Myrrialle Thuleanna<br>
Druid of the 55th Ring<br>

Innoruuk Server</span></td>
