				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Bards and Shaman unite....<a name="39803"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">May 13 04 1:29 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I dont mind at all if shaman or chanter haste is up, even if I am singing haste, overhaste, and proccing haste as well.  Shaman especially. At 65, a shaman who goes OOM in exp groups should really just quit or reroll, there isnt much excuse for it.  With long duration buffs, one cast of haste can last an LDoN or even a smallish raid duration.  
<br />
It doesnt bother me if the melee say haste fading, when they have WoZ and Muse in the song box and DoTB in the buff box.  Am I going to stop twisting my haste?  Am I going to tell them to put song window up?  Am I going to tell the shaman/chanter how to use his/her mana?
<br />
Nope, If they start running low on mana, let THEM tell melees that bard haste is enough, it isnt MY mana.  Im sure other hasting classes know how thier haste stacks up in comparision to other hasting classes haste buffs.
<br />
I like the flexbility to drop a song or two from the twist to HoS, Slow, Lull, Mez, Charm, Gate, Amp and Bombastic Bellow, or do any one of the myriad ways to help the group.  I like the haste already on the Melees, I look at it like insurance, it lets me know that while Daddy is busy elswhere, someone is looking after the kids ;o)</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%"><marquee> <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=370173">
