				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Bards and Shaman unite....<a name="39850"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">May 13 04 5:10 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>65 bard and 65 shaman here<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
As a shaman, I tend to put up Talisman of Alacrity when there's a bard in the group.  It doesn't cost much mana, it lasts almost an hour with SCRM and the coldain 8th shawl, it provides SOME haste if all else fails, and most importantly it makes a little haste icon which is like a security blanket for tanks.
<br />

<br />
I spend a lot more mana and do more good over the course of an hour by keeping ferine avatar up on people, but it's very rare that someone will tell me when that drops.  Haste blinking, tho... I hear about that right away.
<br />

<br />
I know VERY well that it's not necessary.  But it makes melee happy to have it.  It's like AGI - I won't bother explaining how little benefit it gives if someone asks for it, I just cast it. <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
As a bard, I actually notice that the times when DoTB drops are generally the times when I'm trying to CC 2 or 3 mobs, which is when haste would really be quite nice to have so the rest of the group can get them dead and let me stop mezzing. <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />  So I don't mind seeing a shaman or enchanter haste icon.
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
