			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Bards and Shaman unite....<a name="48406"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jun 26 04 1:47 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I also have a 65 shaman, and I do see where Ellorra is coming from as well..  but as far as people &quot;badgering&quot; shaman for haste, I feel that a good deal of that is the people asking for haste do not know any better.  They may not be sure what all your haste songs/proc do, or they are just so used to having haste from a shaman (or enchanter) in their long term buff window that they ask for it without thinking/knowing.
<br />

<br />
On the subject of using Talisman of Alacrity over Swift like the Wind, even with focus and AA extended buffs, ToA lasts SO much longer and is a group buff, and is only 10% less haste, it's a real boon, especially not having to rehaste individuals multiple times in the time it would take one Talisman to wear off.  And really.. when do you hear a Shaman complaining about being out of mana?  Maybe if they are doing all the healing, I suppose maybe, but still.... <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />  Sure if you are out of buff slots, no one is going to have their feelings hurt if Talisman is down and you are playing superior haste, at least not from the shaman's point of view! <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />   
<br />

<br />
Sometimes it's just easier to give the tanks what they want rather than explain.  There are some stubborn people who just want things &quot;their way.&quot;  It's frustrating yes.  I'm also sure some shaman get very much in the habit of casting a &quot;basic buff&quot; set in certain situations, and just are hasting out of habit.  Sometimes you are just so concerned with getting the buffs done it can be an easy thing to do.  
<br />

<br />
I think it's nice to see someone concerned about another class' mana, and I do agree with you about the people ASKING for haste.  But unless you have a clicky for Swift Like the Wind (and even then it still has to be applied individually), ToA is really just a nice compact haste solution for the Shaman.
<br />

<br />
I ramble. Often.<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-10.gif" border="0" alt="Blushing" hspace="2" /></span></td>
