				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Bards and Shaman unite....<a name="48738"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jun 28 04 11:45 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>This is really a two sided argument in which there is no best way in my opinion. However things are done, just leave it be.
<br />

<br />
Its fine to want the shaman to haste the group, the little bit of mana they expend on doing so is insignificant across the duration of the buff.
<br />

<br />
Its also fine to leave the hasting to the bard, when they go for pulls, the mob is mostly dead, and if the bard is chain pulling so quickly as to not have time to keep a haste on the group, then the group will already have enough DPS to not really need to rely on haste.
<br />

<br />
The point here is that a lot of people place a lot of importance on the almighty haste modifier, it really isn't that big a deal in most circumstances. Haste when you can, even if its already there. If the shaman wants to cast haste or not it really wont make a difference since the kill speed will ultimately depend on how fast you bring mobs to the group. If you keep mobs mezz parked, you'll be much more effective than a bard that sings haste for the group the whole time and goes off to pull once the mob is dead or near dead.
<br />

<br />
I've never worried about people asking for a haste buff. It really is a security blanket for many melees, whatever makes them feel comfortable in their roles is a good thing. My role is to maximize through-put of mobs through the party's DPS(as puller), I'm not going to worry about haste as much as how smoothly I can transition the group into the next pull.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
