				<td colspan="2"><span>Couple of things to add/clarify here.  Part of my issue with this is that I dislike redundancy if it can be avoided.  Also with the plethora of traps and nasties casting dots or curses the number of open buff slots becomes an issue, nothing worse than having Malo debuff your Virtue mid fight.
<br />
I have noticed that a lot of shaman are not casting nearly as many buffs either.  Most of the time it's just Fo7, Boar and Tribunal which is grand because the other buffs were somewhat redundant with Fo7 and didn't do a whole lot since Fo7 usually maxed the other stats anyhow.
<br />
My biggest issue with haste are the few whiny buggers out there that have to see that buff in order to feel right.  It's like some sort of security blanket to them that does nothing at all, and for some very strange reason it bugs me *shrug*.
<br />

<br />
Now to clarify a situation I made earlier, which after rereading it does seem quite misleading.
<br />
<blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">First battle:
<br />
Bard sings zek 60% haste, CotM 30% overhaste
<br />
Bard Epic procs for an added 55% haste with str and atk boost</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
This should have been more along the lines of:
<br />
First battle:
<br />
Bard sings zek 60% haste, CotM 30% overhaste
<br />
Bard Epic procs for an add str and atk boost and 55% haste should zek drop
<br />

<br />
Another interesting little ditty I've found is when I'm in a group that does not rely on the shaman hasting.  The shaman gets all gitty because now he/she can toss another nuke or nasty in the battle, especially with caster type mobs.  There were times previously where the shaman and cleric were spending a lot of mana rebuffing because some silly caster mob would sit there and debuff the MT or myself and others.  I do try to pull these with a combo of bellow and mez, but there are times when this isn't totally effective (might be a bug, but I've had a caster mob continue casting after I mezzed and the MT hitting it with an arrow and exactly the same time); aah I long for the days when I could charm pull caster mobs<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-2.gif" border="0" alt="Big Smile" hspace="2" /></span></td>
