				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Bards and Shaman unite....<a name="56794"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 15 04 3:34 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>&quot;Mostly guild group needed a tank last night, so I pulled my largely-retired warrior out of storage and trotted off to BoT. 
<br />

<br />
               The enchanter in the group was casting Vallon AND Wondrous Rapidity. &quot;
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
I think what the chanter was doing was maximizing haste while keeping the stats from VQ up. The highest haste buff in the game is Wonderous Rapidity (70%) but it adds no other stats. Vallons Quickening (66%) on the other hand adds attack and dex i think. Warsong of Zek (60%) also adds even more stats such as str and DS. While the haste portion may be redundant the other stats and effects are not. At least the chance of haste dropping mid fight will be rare<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
I still to this day keep my Songblade effect on even with chanter haste just for the added attack. I guess spell slots aren't much of an issue to me anymore since outside of Uqua my stats are mostly maxed out so I click them off as soon as they are casted on me.
<br />

<br />

<br />
Back to the main topic at hand. I rarely if ever group outside of my circle of friends, guildies included. I am a very reclusive bard you might say but those that do group with me know what every one of my songs does. How is this?....well I educate them. It also helps when my guild leader (warrior) happens to have a lvl65 bard alt. It's kinda funny when in the MA grp and chanter haste fades, all the other war's are asking for chanter haste and my GL simply says, &quot; click your sword please. The other tanks proceed to ask what sword? and my GL explains the effects. Still happens to this day, either he tells them or I do.
<br />

<br />
As far as shaman hasting over me, well lets just say my two closest friends in EQ are shaman so i never have that problem </span></td>
			</tr><tr>
